  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nplease note that this is an issue tracker reserved for bug reports and feature requests.\r\n\r\nFor general questions please use the gitter channel or the Ethereum stack exchange at https://ethereum.stackexchange.com.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth version: 1.8.4-stable\r\nOS & Version: Windows 10\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nGit Commit: 2423ae01e0d2f853512eb2b46954b5ad0754a897\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nScenario : I want to access http://thedapps.com/DAPP-Workbench102/  (a dapp) using my local geth instance started with default IPC geth option. as it's not co hosted so I need to start JSON RPC end point as well.. I have started it using attached JS console using admin API { admin.startRPC('localhost',8545,\"*\") } and tried to access the dapp.. Its did not worked and throw an error **Error: Invalid JSON RPC response: \"\"**\r\n\r\nNote  : when I started GETH instance using normal rpc mode then http://thedapps.com/DAPP-Workbench102/ was connecting fine.\r\n\r\ngeth --rpc --rpcaddr \"localhost\" --rpcport \"8545\" --rpccorsdomain \"*\" --testnet --datadir \"C:\\.......\\BlockChain\\myRopsten\" --identity \"geth-dev\" --syncmode \"light\" --verbosity 4\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nIts did not worked and throw an error **Error: Invalid JSON RPC response: \"\"**\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nStep 1) geth --testnet --datadir \"C:\\........\\BlockChain\\myRopsten\" --identity \"geth-dev\" --syncmode \"light\" --verbosity 4\r\n\r\nThis should start the GETH client exposing IPC interface..\r\n\r\nStep 2) Attached a JS Console geth attach \"\\\\.\\pipe\\geth.ipc\"\r\n\r\nStep 3) Started RPC endpoint admin.startRPC('localhost',8545,\"*\") \r\n\r\nStep 4) Check the URL http://thedapps.com/DAPP-Workbench102/\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n",
